31:59.208 --> 32:02.503
when God didn't pick little green apples,

32:04.297 --> 32:05.131
whatever...

32:09.761 --> 32:11.763
Oh, Denny!

32:13.348 --> 32:14.182
Sunny--

32:15.642 --> 32:16.643
-(bones cracking)
-Ooh!

32:21.898 --> 32:24.609
(sighs) Well, you get the idea.

32:26.402 --> 32:27.236
Sunny...

32:33.326 --> 32:34.786
Sunny Fields, will you marry me?

32:34.869 --> 32:38.706
Oh, Denny, we haven't even been out
on a real date.

32:38.790 --> 32:40.375
Oh, we got plenty of time for that.

32:40.458 --> 32:43.378
Oh, Denny.

32:44.671 --> 32:45.505
I love you.

32:48.007 --> 32:49.926
I'd go to the ends of the earth for you.

32:51.803 --> 32:55.556
Well, you sure make it hard to say no to,
I can tell you that.

32:57.433 --> 32:58.726
Can I think about it overnight?

33:01.771 --> 33:02.605
You can.

33:03.690 --> 33:06.901
-And I'll see you tomorrow?
-I promise.

33:12.198 --> 33:13.032
Good night...

33:14.409 --> 33:15.743
Denny Crane.

33:40.268 --> 33:41.644
I agree with Mr. Shore.

33:42.645 --> 33:45.314
Whatever one wants to call
this nomination process,

33:45.898 --> 33:47.400
it's anything but democratic.

33:48.693 --> 33:51.654
Two political parties pulling the strings.

33:52.113 --> 33:53.823
It's like going to a fast-food restaurant

33:53.906 --> 33:55.366
and being told you can eat
whatever you want.

33:57.160 --> 33:58.661
The menu is fixed.

33:59.829 --> 34:00.955
That having been said,

34:01.414 --> 34:05.126
being a private organization,
the DNC is free to set its own rules.

34:06.044 --> 34:10.715
The only real recourse the people have,
I suppose, is to vote Republican.

34:11.507 --> 34:15.928
And everyone wonders how we ended up
with the likes of George Bush.

34:17.388 --> 34:18.848
-Motion denied.
-(gavel thuds)

34:19.724 --> 34:21.809
Everybody loses.

34:23.895 --> 34:24.771
Well...

34:26.481 --> 34:29.150
The one time I get out
of my tastefully decorated office

34:29.233 --> 34:31.027
to tilt at windmills, and I lose.

34:31.861 --> 34:32.695
I'm sorry.

34:36.491 --> 34:41.704
First of all, I reject the idea
that cloning meat is abusive to cows.

34:42.121 --> 34:43.748
-Why?
-It's meat.

34:43.831 --> 34:45.333
The animal's already dead.

34:45.416 --> 34:48.711
No, Your Honor. It's the cow being cloned
to make the meat.

34:49.045 --> 34:50.463
Did I skip over that?

34:50.838 --> 34:52.548
Dead meat is dead meat.

34:52.632 --> 34:53.925
But... (sighs)

34:54.008 --> 34:56.385
Judgment in favor of the plaintiff.

34:56.469 --> 34:57.553
Oh, there you go.

34:57.637 --> 35:01.224
What-- Judge, we had the same concerns
over artificial insemination

35:01.307 --> 35:03.559
and all the perceived horrors,
and nothing bad happened.

35:03.643 --> 35:05.812
-Judgment for the defendant.
-What?

35:06.646 --> 35:10.149
Whoa, no, no, no. Technology
has not improved the food supply.

35:10.233 --> 35:12.944
-Plaintiff's motion granted.
-Wait.

35:13.027 --> 35:15.029
-You said the defendant's.
-Sustained.

35:15.404 --> 35:19.158
-This guy's worse than me.
-I am the decider.

35:21.494 --> 35:22.328
Adjourned.

35:24.497 --> 35:26.415
-Who won?
-I have no idea.

35:29.794 --> 35:33.172
-So, you have no idea if you won or lost?
-No.

35:33.256 --> 35:35.049
(both chuckle)

35:35.341 --> 35:36.634
I still got the girl though.

35:37.343 --> 35:39.512
When do I get to meet her?

35:39.595 --> 35:42.306
Well, she's due any second.

35:42.390 --> 35:44.559
Alan, I popped the question.

35:46.144 --> 35:48.187
-You did what?
-I love her.

35:49.480 --> 35:52.275
-You asked her to marry you?
-Life is short.

35:52.358 --> 35:55.820
No, Denny. Life can be very long.

35:55.903 --> 35:59.031
Especially when you're bound by law
to the wrong woman.

35:59.115 --> 36:00.908
-You can't--
-She's the right woman.

36:00.992 --> 36:02.952
-You just met her.
-I have a feeling.

36:03.035 --> 36:07.331
Yes, the same one you had about Bev
and five other right women

36:07.415 --> 36:09.584
who turned out to be total disasters.

36:10.418 --> 36:11.294
SUNNY: Knock, knock.

36:11.919 --> 36:14.005
Can't. Still in refractory. (chuckles)

36:15.298 --> 36:18.050
-You must be Sunny.
-Oh, my Sunny.

36:18.801 --> 36:20.469
This is Alan Shore. He was just leaving.

36:21.721 --> 36:23.848
-Howdy, Alan.
-Howdy.

36:24.223 --> 36:25.266
Well, we'll talk later.

36:25.349 --> 36:27.393
-I really think we should talk--
-No, no. Later.

36:33.399 --> 36:35.067
Have we figured out
whether we won our case yet?

36:35.735 --> 36:36.611
Not yet.

36:38.779 --> 36:40.489
So, did I win the girl?

36:41.699 --> 36:45.745
Denny, were you serious when you said
you'd go to the ends of the earth for me?

36:46.162 --> 36:46.996
I was.

36:47.872 --> 36:50.917
-How about Montana?
-What?

36:51.334 --> 36:52.877
I'm moving to Montana in a month.

36:52.960 --> 36:56.214
I would've told you sooner,
but things were going so fast between us.

36:56.964 --> 36:58.633
-Montana?
-I bought a farm there.

36:58.716 --> 37:00.551
Six thousand acres of land.

37:00.635 --> 37:03.471
I'm gonna move my ranch there
and really make a go of it.

37:03.930 --> 37:06.474
-Montana?
-So, the question becomes,

37:07.016 --> 37:09.810
are you really that much of a cowboy,
Denny Crane?

37:12.355 --> 37:13.189
What?

37:15.858 --> 37:16.692
Well, uh...

37:18.236 --> 37:19.320
my life is here.

37:19.820 --> 37:22.698
Well, one day,
you will have to go to pasture.

37:23.282 --> 37:24.700
Maybe now's the time.

37:26.369 --> 37:28.663
Ride into the sunset with me, Denny Crane.

37:32.500 --> 37:34.126
See, it's... it's, um...

37:36.379 --> 37:37.296
It's not the job.

37:38.714 --> 37:39.799
It's someone else.

37:42.426 --> 37:45.137
Oh. Someone else.

37:45.221 --> 37:48.057
Uh, my best friend.
That was him you just met.

37:49.934 --> 37:51.269
Are you serious?

37:52.687 --> 37:55.982
See, uh, we meet every night

37:56.065 --> 37:59.568
for, uh, cigars and scotch.

37:59.944 --> 38:01.654
It's a standing...

38:03.364 --> 38:06.617
-Why don't you stay here?
-I just bought a business.

38:09.120 --> 38:10.162
I have to go.

38:13.666 --> 38:16.711
If you'd rather stay and drink scotch
and smoke cigars,

38:16.794 --> 38:19.338
well, maybe that tells us something.

38:19.422 --> 38:23.050
But this has no bearing
on my love for you.

38:25.428 --> 38:27.305
-It's just--
-Your love for him.

38:31.642 --> 38:35.313
I can't go to Montana.

38:49.827 --> 38:51.579
Just like that, it's over?

38:54.165 --> 38:56.292
She turned me down. What can I do?

38:59.837 --> 39:01.714
-I'm sorry, Denny.
-No, you're not.

39:02.882 --> 39:05.343
-You're relieved.
-Well, I'm that, too.

39:05.426 --> 39:07.928
But if you truly loved her,
then I am sorry.

39:10.973 --> 39:13.642
-Denny?
-There's no need to be sorry, Alan.

39:14.185 --> 39:18.522
Love, even when it's fleeting,
even if it's for a day or two, it's...

39:21.442 --> 39:22.818
it's everything.

39:26.614 --> 39:28.032
Don't you agree?

39:32.036 --> 39:36.123
I do. I actually think it's why
I'm still single.

39:38.918 --> 39:41.879
Every morning I get to wake up and wonder,
"Will this be the day?"

39:41.962 --> 39:47.176
Every night I put my head on my pillow
and wonder, "Will I meet her tomorrow?"

39:47.968 --> 39:49.762
I imagine what she'll look like.

39:50.429 --> 39:54.308
Her smile, the way she does her hair,
how she laughs,

39:56.143 --> 39:59.063
the contour of her breasts, neck.

40:02.108 --> 40:05.111
The promise of love can be everything.

40:08.364 --> 40:11.534
It's a magic you rarely find in marriage
though. Maybe you lucked out.

40:11.617 --> 40:15.413
You don't believe married people
can stay in love?

40:15.746 --> 40:16.580
Oh.

40:18.290 --> 40:21.252
I believe they can know
even more profound joys,

40:21.335 --> 40:23.087
be it with children,

40:24.630 --> 40:26.173
the depth of the relationship itself.

40:26.257 --> 40:29.969
It can evolve into something
they can't possibly live without.

40:30.761 --> 40:34.432
Yet, it's something that doesn't quite

40:35.724 --> 40:38.394
so resemble love.

40:39.353 --> 40:41.272
At least not the romance of love.

40:41.856 --> 40:44.608
-I never knew you to be such a romantic.
-(scoffs)

40:45.734 --> 40:47.403
My problem is I'm too romantic.

40:48.362 --> 40:51.031
No woman can possibly measure up
to the promise of tomorrow

40:51.115 --> 40:52.408
that love holds for me.

40:54.952 --> 40:55.870
What about me?

40:57.455 --> 40:58.747
Well, it's not the same.

41:01.375 --> 41:05.087
-You know one thing I do love about you?
-Tell me.

41:06.088 --> 41:09.133
While many people embrace
the promise of tomorrow,

41:10.384 --> 41:13.095
too few celebrate the...

41:14.388 --> 41:16.223
joy of now.

41:16.849 --> 41:20.686
And nobody does that like Denny Crane.

41:23.397 --> 41:24.857
Well, let me tell you something.

41:25.983 --> 41:30.196
When you got polar ice caps melting
and breaking off into big chunks,

41:30.279 --> 41:33.824
and you got Osama still hiding in a cave
planning his next attack,

41:33.908 --> 41:36.952
when you got other rogue nations
with nuclear arsenals,

41:37.036 --> 41:41.081
and not to mention
some whack-job homegrown

41:41.165 --> 41:45.794
who can cancel you at any second,
and when you got...

41:48.088 --> 41:49.006
mad cow...

41:51.050 --> 41:53.719
"now" gets high priority.

41:54.845 --> 41:58.766
And when you're sitting on the balcony
on a clear night,

42:01.060 --> 42:02.937
sipping scotch with your best friend,

42:07.399 --> 42:09.944
"now" is everything.

42:13.989 --> 42:14.823
Here's to now.

42:17.993 --> 42:19.203
Here's to now.

42:31.882 --> 42:33.801
MALE NARRATOR:<i> Two weeks</i>
<i>from tonight on </i>Boston Legal...

42:33.884 --> 42:35.761
-May I help you?
-I seek to be a priest.

42:35.844 --> 42:40.182
Of all the ridiculous, sacrilegious acts
of heresy I've ever heard!

42:40.266 --> 42:41.350
God beckoned me.

42:41.433 --> 42:43.644
-I was arrested last night.
-I don't think we can represent you.

42:44.103 --> 42:46.772
They'll most likely ask you to flip
your employer, and that would be Lorraine.

42:46.855 --> 42:48.399
You kept from me you were a call girl.

42:48.482 --> 42:50.651
I won't be judged for it,
especially by you.

42:50.734 --> 42:52.653
How would you feel
about running for president?

42:52.736 --> 42:54.280
-President?
-Do they know you have mad cow?

42:54.363 --> 42:56.073
They're looking
for the next Ronald Reagan.

42:56.156 --> 42:58.284
Ronald Reagan didn't have a hooker fetish.

42:58.367 --> 43:00.286
Denny Crane, commander-in-chief.

43:00.369 --> 43:01.704
I like it.

43:03.205 --> 43:05.207
(closing theme playing)
